Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the stems from the @Portobello Mushrooms{2}(whole) (but leave the mushroom whole).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Fry the mushrooms until golden brown, ~{4-5%minutes}, then turn over and cook for a further ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%grams} into thirds, halving any thick stems lengthways.

Trim and peel the @Carrot{1}(trimmed and peeled). Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Reduce the heat to low, then add the @Ginger Puree{15%grams} and @Butter{20%grams} to the pan. Baste the mushrooms by gently spooning over the ginger butter.

Transfer the mushrooms, stem-side up, to a medium #baking tray{}. Once the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until tender, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, boil a full #kettle{} for the noodles.

Pour the boiled water into a medium #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring to a boil. Add the @Egg Noodle Nest{125%grams} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

While everything cooks, return the (now empty) frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{} (no need to clean).

Once the oil is hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{1%pack} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Once the chicken is cooked, set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Next, add the Tenderstem® to the pan and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of @water{50%ml}, then cover with a #lid{} (or foil) and cook until tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Remove the lid, then add the carrot ribbons and @Ginger, Garlic & Lemongrass Puree{15%grams} and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @Soy Sauce{25%ml}, @Ketjap Manis{50%grams}, @Honey{15%grams}, @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml} in the pan. Bring to a boil, then simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}.

> If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Add the cooked chicken and noodles to the pan and simmer until piping hot, tossing to coat in the sauce, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When ready, thinly slice the cooked mushrooms.

Share the chicken and veg noodles between your bowls and top with the sliced mushrooms.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%grams} to finish.

Enjoy!